body:
Hey people. I wanted to make a post discussing all the toxic people you have played with on the OCE server. I totally am all for name dropping. Perhaps they will see this post themselves and might start to reform after seeing that the community hates they way they act. 

My recent player goes by the name of _Name Removed_.
He was playing Riven on the enemy team. From the get go, my team could tell this was going to be the typical toxic, trash talking Riven player that im sure everyone has seen in the past. At about 10mins he was 0-5 in lane and what do you know, the trolling begins. &quot;I dont care about this game anymore&quot; &quot;Just end, im plat, all you guys will be stuck in silver/gold&quot; &quot;1v1 me, ill **** you up.&quot;

Hawwmahhgawwd it was just pathetic. A real child. Then instead of actually helping his team he was just coming at us 5v1 etc, intent feeding. {{item:3070}} 

How are people really this salty? Instead of brushing the loss off and getting ready for the next game, he then starts calling out people to 1v1 him in post game lobby. I watched the chat for a bit then i decided to accept the challenge. Maybe he did have a bad game and was actually a really good player? I like a challenge anyhow. So he lists off the rules etc calls me a pussy a few times and then makes the game. He picks viktor into my Syndra. (I have quite a bit of experience at Syndra and i wasnt going to let this punk win.)  It was over as soon as the level 3 poped. I already had his flash by that point, so it was a simple QEW Ignite combo to finish him off. 

He then leaves the game and what do you know, the trash talking begins AGAIN! &quot;Can only play op champs? Youre so shit.&quot;

Anyway! Please leave your story! Dont forget to _not_ name drop.
